like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q135","QuestionID":"QID135"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID259","SecondaryAttribute":"Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i>","DataExportTag":"Q259","QuestionID":"QID259"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID320","SecondaryAttribute":"First though, take a moment to think about one of the best lessons you have received. It could be...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"First though, take a moment to think about  one of the <i>best lessons <\/i>you have received. It could be from a class, a book, online.  Try to think of what the lesson said, and what you learned.<br><br>In this study, we will show you a lesson and then ask you questions like the following: \u201cHow much insight did that lesson give you?\u201d  If you were to answer this question for the \u201cbest lesson you've ever received\u201d you would mark \u201cA great deal.\u201d To confirm that you understand this instruction please click \u201cA great deal\u201d below:<br>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q320","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"First though, take a moment to think about one of the best lessons you have received. It could be...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID320"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID68","SecondaryAttribute":"Given this, please again take moment to reflect on how much you learned from first passage\u00a0you re..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Given this, please again take moment to reflect on how much you learned from <b>first passage&nbsp;<\/b>you read, overall. (Repeat: The first thing you read, <b>NOT<\/b> the above text.) You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q68","QuestionID":"QID68","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Given this, please again take moment to reflect on how much you learned from first passage\u00a0you re...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID89","SecondaryAttribute":"Given this, please again take moment to reflect on how much you learned from the case you read, o...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Given this, please again take moment to reflect on how much you learned from <b>the case <\/b>you read, overall. (<b>The first thing you read, NOT the above text.<\/b>) You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Given this, please again take moment to reflect on how much you learned from the case you read, o...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on how much you learned beyond this summary, we'd like you to rerate the information. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.","DataExportTag":"Q89","QuestionID":"QID89"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID274","SecondaryAttribute":"Giving away your product to social media influencers can be an inexpensive but effective way of m...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Giving away your product to social media influencers can be an inexpensive but effective way of marketing.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Giving away your product to social media influencers can be an inexpensive but effective way of m...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i>","DataExportTag":"Q274","QuestionID":"QID274"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID190","SecondaryAttribute":"Here is all the information given by the business professor once more: The case: Dutch bicycle ma...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Here is all the information given by the business professor once more:<br><\/b><br><b>The case:<\/b><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br><br><b>The message: <\/b><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Here is all the information given by the business professor once more: The case: Dutch bicycle ma...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Here is the real-world case again:<br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<\/i><br><br><i>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<\/i><br><br><i>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q190","QuestionID":"QID190"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID199","SecondaryAttribute":"Here is all the information given by the business professor once more: The message: Companies tha...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Here is all the information given by the business professor once more:<\/b><i><br><\/i><br><b>The message:<\/b><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br><br><b>The case:<\/b><br><i>\n\nDutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Here is all the information given by the business professor once more: The message: Companies tha...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Here is the message again:<i><br><\/i><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q199","QuestionID":"QID199"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID130","SecondaryAttribute":"Here is the case again: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Here is the case again:<br><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q130","QuestionID":"QID130","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Here is the case again: D