ation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"RecodeValues":{"2":"1","3":"2","4":"3","5":"4","7":"5","8":"6","9":"7"},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":10,"NextAnswerId":3,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","DataExportTag":"v.m2_t","QuestionID":"QID297"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID305","SecondaryAttribute":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","Choices":{"2":{"Display":"Not valuable at all"},"3":{"Display":"Of almost no value"},"4":{"Display":"A little valuable"},"5":{"Display":"Somewhat valuable"},"7":{"Display":"Moderately valuable"},"8":{"Display":"Very valuable"},"9":{"Display":"Extremely valuable"}},"ChoiceOrder":["2","3","4","5","7","8","9"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":10,"NextAnswerId":3,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","RecodeValues":{"2":"1","3":"2","4":"3","5":"4","7":"5","8":"6","9":"7"},"DataExportTag":"v.m1_j","QuestionID":"QID305"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID312","SecondaryAttribute":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","Choices":{"2":{"Display":"Not valuable at all"},"3":{"Display":"Of very little value"},"4":{"Display":"A little valuable"},"5":{"Display":"Somewhat valuable"},"7":{"Display":"Moderately valuable"},"8":{"Display":"Very valuable"},"9":{"Display":"Extremely valuable"}},"ChoiceOrder":["2","3","4","5","7","8","9"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"RecodeValues":{"2":"1","3":"2","4":"3","5":"4","7":"5","8":"6","9":"7"},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":10,"NextAnswerId":3,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","DataExportTag":"v.m2_j","QuestionID":"QID312"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID56","SecondaryAttribute":"In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital co...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital co...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Please review what you originally read.<br><\/i><br>A company named VanMoof reported that more than 25 percent of its bikes were damaged before even being delivered. \"Your covetable products, your frictionless website, your killer brand\u200a\u2014\u200athey all count for nothing when your delivery partner drops the ball,\" said Bex Rad, Vanmoof's creative director.<br><br>The solution? Reconsider the packaging. \"We asked ourselves, what do Americans really love? What would prompt couriers to be delicate with a parcel?\" VanMoof co-founder Taco Carlier said.<br><br>A TV was the obvious answer.\n\nA big-screen TV box is roughly the same size and weight as a bike box. So to convince shippers to handle its products with more care, VanMoof began printing photos of TVs on its packaging. The boxes still depicted the bike, too, but at a glance it does look like you would find a massive widescreen TV inside instead of a high-end commuter bike.<br><br>Damages dropped by 80 percent since then, according to the company. Even after a reporter revealed the trick, the drop in damages has stayed consistent.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q56","QuestionID":"QID56"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID13","SecondaryAttribute":"In 2001, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but decided the rival company\u2019s market was laugh.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"In 2001, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but decided the rival company\u2019s market was laughably niche. Come 2011, Netflix was worth 13 billion, and perhaps because of their decision, Blockbuster was bankrupt.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"sp.bg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"In 2001, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but decided the rival company\u2019s market was laugh...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID13"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID214","SecondaryAttribute":"In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizz...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizz...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\n<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.\n<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i>","DataExportTag":"Q214","QuestionID":"QID214"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID221","SecondaryAttribute":"In 2016, Jean-Philippe Courtois was put in charge of Microsoft\u2019s global sales and operations (ove.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>In 2016, Jean-Philippe Courtois was put in charge of Microsoft\u2019s global sales and operations (over 40,000 people) as the company shifted to cloud based software. To best accommodate this change, Courtois decided to replace the company\u2019s training on anticipating customer questions with training on listening to customers, and scrapped lengthy performance reviews for coaching opportunities on interpersonal skills. Despite a huge transition to a cloud-based infrastructure, Microsoft saw a $19 million rise in revenue from 2016 to 2018 \u2013 mostly thanks to satisfied customers.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"In 2016, Jean-Philippe Courtois was put in charge of Microsoft\u2019s global sales and operations (ove...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\n<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.\n<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i>","DataExportTag":"Q221","QuestionID":"QID221"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID14","SecondaryAttribute":"Late in post-production for Jurassic Park, director Steven Spielberg cut top-quality stop-motion...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Late in post-production for Jurassic Park, director Steven Spielberg cut top-quality stop-motion models of the dinosaurs to try never-before-used computer generated renderings. This risky change may have helped the movie to break box office records.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"sp.gg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Late in post-production for Jurassic Park, director Steven Spielberg cut top-quality stop-motion...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID14"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID36","SecondaryAttribute":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now how much do you think the above taught you?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"t.n2","QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Nothing"},"2":{"Display":"A lot"}},"QuestionID":"QID36"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID43","SecondaryAttribute":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now how much do you think the above taught you?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Nothing"},"2":{"Display":"A lot"}},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","DataExportTag":"t.g2","QuestionID":"QID43"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID84","SecondaryAttribute":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the information. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the information. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.","DataExportTag":"Q84","QuestionID":"QID84"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID37","SecondaryAttribute":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"a.n2","QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Very much so"}},"QuestionID":"QID37"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID44","SecondaryAttribute":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Very much so"}},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","DataExportTag":"a.g2","QuestionID":"QID44"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID322","SecondaryAttribute":"Now, let's consider the other extreme. Try to remember one of the worst lessons you've ever recei...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Now, let's consider the other extreme. <br><br>Try to remember one of the <i>worst lessons<\/i> you've ever received -- again it could be from an article, video, class, or relative. Whatever you were taught could have even seemed interesting, but turned out to be totally empty or meaningless. This kind of lesson should get a \"None\" on the scale below.&nbsp;Please fill out the scale accordingly.<br>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q322","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now, let's consider the other extreme. Try to remember one of the worst lessons you've ever recei...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID322"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID125","SecondaryAttribute":"Now, please rate the bolded information above.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Now, please rate the bolded information above.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q125","QuestionID":"QID125","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now, please rate the bolded information above.","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID75","SecondaryAttribute":"Overall, which statement do you find more insightful?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Overall, which statement do you find more insightful?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"choice","QuestionID":"QID75","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Overall, which statement do you find more insightful?","Choices":{"4":{"Display":"In 2000, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but thought the rival company\u2019s market was laughably niche. Come 2011, Netflix was worth 13 billion, and because of their decision, Blockbuster was bankrupt."},"5":{"Display":"Companies, corporations, or industries that do not have the foresight to anticipate future consumer desires and preferences will always find themselves pushing outdated products and unable to turn a profit."}},"ChoiceOrder":["4","5"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"Randomization":{"Advanced":null,"Type":"All","TotalRandSubset":""}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID38","SecondaryAttribute":"Please enter your unique prolific ID below","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please enter your unique prolific ID below","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"id","QuestionID":"QID38","QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please enter your unique prolific ID below","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"SearchSource":{"AllowFreeResponse":"false"}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID33","SecondaryAttribute":"Please explain what additional information is provided by the statement chose (in comparison to t...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please explain what additional information is provided by the statement chose (in comparison to the other).","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"qual","QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please explain what additional information is provided by the statement chose (in comparison to t...","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"MinChar","MinChars":"6"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"SearchSource":{"AllowFreeResponse":"false"},"QuestionID":"QID33"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID1717485714","SecondaryAttribute":"Please give your age below (in years)","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please give your age below (in years)","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please give your age below (in years)","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"ContentType","MinChars":"1","TotalChars":"1","ContentType":"ValidNumber","ValidDateType":"DateWithFormat","ValidPhone