 case study:","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with a real-world case study.","DataExportTag":"Q134","QuestionID":"QID134"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID167","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with the following message.","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor gave the following message.","DataExportTag":"Q167","QuestionID":"QID167"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID83","SecondaryAttribute":"The information you were shown derives from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof f...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>The information you were shown derives from this case study:<br><\/i><br><b>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\n<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>The company came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found instantaneous results: shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q83","QuestionID":"QID83","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The information you were shown derives from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof f...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID2","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case: Companies that package their pr...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"hypothetical","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case: Companies that package their pr...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID2"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID160","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. Please read it...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. <u>Please read it closely.<\/u><\/b><u><br><\/u><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. Please read it...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q160","QuestionID":"QID160"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID132","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. Please read it...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. <u>Please read it closely.<\/u><\/b><br>\n<br>\n<span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><\/span>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q132","QuestionID":"QID132","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. Please read it...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9SsLUX1YLBxRm6i","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID143","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was: Companies that package their pr...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br>\n<br>\n<span style=\"color:#27ae60;\"><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><\/span>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was: Companies that package their pr...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"Questio